en_223096_0	Thirty-three people have died in a heat wave that has baked the southern part of the Canadian province of Quebec.
en_223096_1	The sweltering weather began last Friday with temperatures hitting 35C and high humidity.
en_223096_2	The death toll has climbed every day this week, with most of the victims between the ages of 50 to 80.
en_223096_3	The heat wave is the worst the province has seen in decades.
en_223096_4	Officials are urging people to drink plenty of water and stay in the shade.
